#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (_pācittiya_)"

#. HTML: </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:0.4"
msgid "Bhūtagāmavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 17"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:0.5"
msgid "17. Nikkaḍḍhanasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on throwing out"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.44, pts-cs-bu-pc17.1, pts-vp-en.2.250, ms2V_428
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū aññataraṃ paccantimaṃ mahāvihāraṃ paṭisaṅkharonti—"
msgstr "At that time the monks from the group of seventeen were repairing a large dwelling nearby,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.3"
msgid "“idha mayaṃ vassaṃ vasissāmā”ti."
msgstr "intending to stay there for the rainy season."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.4"
msgid "Addasaṃsu kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū sattarasavaggiye bhikkhū vihāraṃ paṭisaṅkharonte."
msgstr "The monks from the group of six saw this"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.5"
msgid "Disvāna evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.6"
msgid "“ime, āvuso, sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū vihāraṃ paṭisaṅkharonti."
msgstr "“These monks from the group of seventeen are repairing a dwelling."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.7"
msgid "Handa ne vuṭṭhāpessāmā”ti."
msgstr "Let’s throw them out.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.8"
msgid "Ekacce evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "But some of them said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.9"
msgid "“āgamethāvuso, yāva paṭisaṅkharonti; paṭisaṅkhate vuṭṭhāpessāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Let’s wait until they’ve finished repairing it.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms2V_429
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.10"
msgid "Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū sattarasavaggiye bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the monks from the group of six said to those from the group of seventeen,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.11"
msgid "“uṭṭhethāvuso, amhākaṃ vihāro pāpuṇātī”ti."
msgstr "“Leave, we get this dwelling.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: paṭikacceva → paṭigacceva (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.12"
msgid "“Nanu, āvuso, paṭikacceva ācikkhitabbaṃ, mayañcaññaṃ paṭisaṅkhareyyāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Shouldn’t you have told us beforehand? We would’ve repaired another one.”"

#. HTML: </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.13"
msgid "“Nanu, āvuso, saṃghiko vihāro”ti?"
msgstr "“Doesn’t this dwelling belong to the Order?”"

#. HTML: </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.14"
msgid "“Āmāvuso, saṃghiko vihāro”ti."
msgstr "“Yes it does.”"

#. HTML: </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.15"
msgid "“Uṭṭhethāvuso, amhākaṃ vihāro pāpuṇātī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, leave; we get this dwelling.”"

#. HTML: </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.16"
msgid "“Mahallako, āvuso, vihāro."
msgstr "“The dwelling is large."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.17"
msgid "Tumhepi vasatha, mayampi vasissāmā”ti."
msgstr "You can stay here and so can we.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.251
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.18"
msgid "“Uṭṭhethāvuso, amhākaṃ vihāro pāpuṇātī”ti kupitā anattamanā gīvāyaṃ gahetvā nikkaḍḍhanti."
msgstr "But they said, “Leave, we get this dwelling,” and they grabbed them by the neck and threw them out in anger."

#. HTML: </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.19"
msgid "Te nikkaḍḍhīyamānā rodanti."
msgstr "The monks from the group of seventeen cried."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.20"
msgid "Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—“kissa tumhe, āvuso, rodathā”ti?"
msgstr "When other monks asked them why,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.21"
msgid "“Ime, āvuso, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kupitā anattamanā amhe saṃghikā vihārā nikkaḍḍhantī”ti."
msgstr "they told them what had happened."

#. HTML: </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.22"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.23"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.24"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kupitā anattamanā bhikkhū saṃghikā vihārā nikkaḍḍhissantī”ti."
msgstr "“How can the monks from the group of six angrily throw other monks out of a dwelling belonging to the Order?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, ms2V_430
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.25"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master.…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.26"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, kupitā anattamanā bhikkhū saṃghikā vihārā nikkaḍḍhathā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.27"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.28"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.29"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, kupitā anattamanā bhikkhū saṃghikā vihārā nikkaḍḍhissatha?"
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you angrily throw other monks out of a dwelling belonging to the Order?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.30"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.31"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.31a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc4, ms2V_431
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:1.32"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ kupito anattamano saṃghikā vihārā nikkaḍḍheyya vā nikkaḍḍhāpeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk, in anger, throws another monk out of a dwelling belonging to the Order, or gets him thrown out, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc5, pts-cs-bu-pc17.2.1, ms2V_432
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "…The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc6, pts-vp-pli4.45, ms2V_433
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.1.6"
msgid "Bhikkhunti"
msgstr "Another monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.1.7"
msgid "aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ."
msgstr "a different monk."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc7, ms2V_434
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.1.8"
msgid "Kupito anattamanoti"
msgstr "In anger:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.1.9"
msgid "anabhiraddho āhatacitto khilajāto."
msgstr "discontent, having hatred, hostile."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc8, ms2V_435
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.1.10"
msgid "Saṃghiko nāma"
msgstr "A dwelling belonging to the Order:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.1.11"
msgid "vihāro saṃghassa dinno hoti pariccatto."
msgstr "given to the Order, given up to the Order."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc9, ms2V_436
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.1.12"
msgid "Nikkaḍḍheyyāti"
msgstr "Throws out:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.252
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.1.13"
msgid "gabbhe gahetvā pamukhaṃ nikkaḍḍhati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "if he takes hold of him in a room and throws him out to the porch, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.1.14"
msgid "Pamukhe gahetvā bahi nikkaḍḍhati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If he takes hold of him on the porch and throws him outside, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.1.15"
msgid "Ekena payogena bahukepi dvāre atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "Even if he makes him go through many doors with a single effort, he commits one offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, ms2V_437
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.1.16"
msgid "Nikkaḍḍhāpeyyāti"
msgstr "Gets […] thrown out:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
#. VAR: pācittiyassa → dukkaṭassa (pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.1.17"
msgid "aññaṃ āṇāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "if he asks another, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.1.18"
msgid "Sakiṃ āṇatto bahukepi dvāre atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If he only asks once, then even if the other makes him go through many doors, he commits one offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc11, pts-cs-bu-pc17.2.2, ms2V_438
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.2.1"
msgid "Saṃghike saṃghikasaññī kupito anattamano nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it belongs to the Order, and he perceives it as belonging to the Order, and in anger he throws him out or gets him thrown out, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.2.2"
msgid "Saṃghike vematiko kupito anattamano nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it belongs to the Order, but he is unsure if it does, and in anger he throws him out or gets him thrown out, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.2.3"
msgid "Saṃghike puggalikasaññī kupito anattamano nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it belongs to the Order, but he perceives it as belonging to an individual, and in anger he throws him out or gets him thrown out, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12, ms2V_439
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.2.4"
msgid "Tassa parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he throws out one of his requisites, or he gets it thrown out, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.2.5"
msgid "Vihārassa upacārā vā upaṭṭhānasālāya vā maṇḍapā vā rukkhamūlā vā ajjhokāsā vā nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he throws him out or gets him thrown out from the vicinity of a dwelling, from an assembly-hall, from under a roof-cover, from the foot of a tree, or from a space out in the open, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.2.6"
msgid "Tassa parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he throws out one of his requisites from any of these places, or he gets it thrown out, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.2.7"
msgid "Anupasampannaṃ vihārā vā vihārassa upacārā vā upaṭṭhānasālāya vā maṇḍapā vā rukkhamūlā vā ajjhokāsā vā nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he throws out one who is not fully ordained, or gets them thrown out, from a dwelling, from the vicinity of a dwelling, from an assembly-hall, from under a roof-cover, from the foot of a tree, or from a space out in the open, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.2.8"
msgid "Tassa parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he throws out one of his requisites from any of these places, or gets it thrown out, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13, ms2V_440
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.2.9"
msgid "Puggalike saṃghikasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it belongs to an individual, but he perceives it as belonging to the Order, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.2.10"
msgid "Puggalike vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it belongs to an individual, but he is unsure if it does, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.253
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.2.11"
msgid "Puggalike puggalikasaññī aññassa puggalike āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it belongs to an individual, and he perceives it as belonging to an individual, but that individual is not himself, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.2.12"
msgid "Attano puggalike anāpatti."
msgstr "If it belongs to himself, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc14, pts-cs-bu-pc17.2.3, ms2V_441
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.3.2"
msgid "alajjiṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,"
msgstr "if he throws out, or gets thrown out, one who is shameless;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.3.3"
msgid "tassa parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,"
msgstr "if he throws out, or gets thrown out, a requisite belonging to that person;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.3.4"
msgid "ummattakaṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,"
msgstr "if he throws out, or gets thrown out, one who is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.3.5"
msgid "tassa parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,"
msgstr "if he throws out, or gets thrown out, a requisite belonging to that person;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.3.6"
msgid "bhaṇḍanakārakaṃ kalahakārakaṃ vivādakārakaṃ bhassakārakaṃ saṃghe adhikaraṇakārakaṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,"
msgstr "if he throws out, or gets thrown out, one who is quarrelsome and disputatious, who creates legal issues in the Order;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.3.7"
msgid "tassa parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,"
msgstr "if he throws out, or gets thrown out, a requisite belonging to that person;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.3.8"
msgid "antevāsikaṃ vā saddhivihārikaṃ vā na sammā vattantaṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,"
msgstr "if he throws out, or gets thrown out, a pupil or student who is not conducting himself properly;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.3.9"
msgid "tassa parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,"
msgstr "if he throws out, or gets thrown out, a requisite belonging to that person;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.3.10"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.3.11"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc15, ms2V_442
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:2.3.12"
msgid "Nikkaḍḍhanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ."
msgstr "The seventh rule, the training rule on throwing out, is finished."
